<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 31 at 7:27PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...PATCHY TO AREAS OF DENSE FOG FOR NEW YEARS EVE...
Rain and light winds have allowed fog to form in most areas. The
visibilities will fluctuate between one-quarter mile to 3 miles at
times through this evening.
Those traveling across the region, should be prepared for rapid
changes in visibility. Use extreme caution, use low beam
headlights and increase following distance with other vehicles.</description>
